W_1 = tf.Variable(tf.truncated_normal([3, 3, 3, 16], stddev=0.1), name="W_1")
b_1 = tf.constant(0.1, shape=[16], name="b_1")
conv_1 = tf.nn.conv2d(x, W_1, strides=[1, 2, 2, 1], padding='SAME', name="conv_1")
# PRelu
pos = tf.nn.relu(conv_1)
neg = -0.1 * (conv_1 - tf.abs(conv_1)) * 0.5
h_conv1 = pos + neg

here is the error:
Running model failed: Invalid argument: No OpKernel was registered to support Op 'Abs' with these attrs [[Node: Abs = Abs[T=DT_FLOAT](conv_1)]]

It seems that the little part tf.abs(conv_1)) can be frozen but not imported in the mobile

body:
It's me again, i've tried something else and found a new error, here is the piece of code:

``` python
W_1 = tf.Variable(tf.truncated_normal([3, 3, 3, 16], stddev=0.1), name="W_1")
b_1 = tf.constant(0.1, shape=[16], name="b_1")
conv_1 = tf.nn.conv2d(x, W_1, strides=[1, 2, 2, 1], padding='SAME', name="conv_1")
# PRelu
pos = tf.nn.relu(conv_1)
neg = -0.1 * (conv_1 - tf.abs(conv_1)) * 0.5
h_conv1 = pos + neg
```

here is the error:
`Running model failed: Invalid argument: No OpKernel was registered to support Op 'Abs' with these attrs
     [[Node: Abs = Abs[T=DT_FLOAT](conv_1)]]`

It seems that the little part `tf.abs(conv_1))` can be frozen but not imported in the mobile
